         <div>
            <head>15.11.1882 Mittwoch</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49069">Hamburg</placeName>. November. 15. 1882</p>
            <p> Got up early. The ice on the piece of ground we flooded last night is quite useless
               and bad, so I smashed it up. When I came home from school I saw the <persName key="1175">M. Andriez</persName> and <persName key="1155">Ward</persName> had
               flooded the ground anew. The water froze almost as soon as it got to a standstill. A
               Candidate was to come today as <persName key="1162">pastor Blümer</persName> was out
               to superintend us as <persName key="1162">P. Blümer</persName> was out, so <persName key="1175">Andriez</persName> and I were making plans with <persName key="1156">Robert</persName>
               <note type="reg">Blümer</note> how to tease him a little and as
                  <persName key="1155">Ward</persName> came into the room we told <persName key="1156">Robert</persName> to go away as we did not want his <persName key="1162">father</persName> to notice that we were all in the same room, and as
               he would not go, <persName key="1175">Andriez</persName> told him we were going to
               speak French; he went away in a rage swore he would tell his <persName key="1162">father</persName> who would beat <persName key="1155">Ward</persName>, <persName key="1175">Andriez</persName> and me and at last went and streaked to his
                  mother<note type="reg">
                  <persName key="1163">Auguste</persName>
               </note>.
                  <persName key="1155">Ward</persName> in trying to show off his skill in balancing
               bottles, after nearly breaking his nose, broke a beer bottle. Among other things that
               happened at tea to night there was a dearth of bread in which <persName key="1156">Robert</persName> tried to be very important, and bustled about with a face as
               long as the <persName key="1162">pastors</persName> umbrella, which is a woollen one
               and of a pretty good size.</p>
